cfallin commented on PR #10827:

This is low-effort AI spam: "wast" is not a typo for "waste", it is a file format in the Wasm world. Similarly, "filetests" is our canonical spelling for our test framework, and "re-use" is a valid spelling of "reuse".

Making such PRs without even a small amount of effort to double-check is grossly disrespectful to maintainers' time and I will close this PR now.
